title: For Sale:  Sig 1911 Ultra Compact Nitron .45 ACP, Excellent Cond!
postcontent:
Ok, I never planned to sell this gun, but new firearm interests necessitate selling this one, so here it is..

Up for sale is my Sig Sauer 1911 Ultra compact in .45 ACP. This gun is is excellent condition with exactly 200 rounds downrange (in other words, barely broken in). 

In case you are unfamiliar with the model, this is a officer's 1911. It holds just one less round than a full size 1911, but in a much smaller, lighter, easy to conceal package. This has been my daily carry since I got it, and has been by my side almost daily. The gun has a black nitron finish, which if you know Sigs, you know is tough as nails. It comes with an extended magazine release, a checkered front strap, steel mainspring housing, novak cut night sights that glow very bright, a beavertail grip safety with memory pad, skeleton combat hammer, adjustable skeletonized trigger, and tons of other upgrades that 1911 enthusiasts look for. The trigger on this gun breaks crisp and clean, making it a dream to shoot. Its far more accurate than I am. I did A LOT of research before settling on this gun, and the only reason I'm parting with it is to fund the purchase of another 1911 that's on the pricey side.

Included with the gun are the sig hard case, paperwork, three sig factory magazines, and one wilson combat magazine for max reliability when carrying. Also included with the stock blackwood grips are a set of Raasco rosewood grips and black box elderwood grips that both look classy as hell (see pics). I'll also throw in a remora in the waistband holster with sweatshield that makes carry comfortable and easy. This gun has been meticulously cared for like all my firearms.

I am asking $925, which is pretty fair considering all I'm including. I saw one of these at Outpost armory in Murfreesboro today going for $1060.

Must be a TN resident and be able to legally own a handgun. Must have valid TN driver's license (carry permit preferred), and be willing to meet face to face and fill out a bill of sale. 

Feel free to email me with any questions. Thanks for looking!

title: For Sale:  Brand New VZ58 - 2008 100% MD Compliant  7.62x39 :-)

THESE ARE THE LAST ONES - OBAMA IMPORT BAN PREVENTS FUTURE SHIPMENTS :-(

********************** GET THEM WHILE THEY LAST **************************

The VZ58 - 2008 V (Výsadkový—"airborne"), features a side-folding metal shoulder stock.
 Dubbed the VZ2008, this carbine sports the side-folding steel stock and features a combination of original Czech and new US-made parts for legality.
 light and compact handling characteristics of the carbine. With the stock folded, the 7-pound VZ2008 measures just over 26 inches long. This compact size, combined with the powerful 7.62x39mm chambering and 30 + 1 capacity makes it extremely well suited as a law enforcement patrol rifle.
 Over the course of a few hundred rounds, the rifle performed without a hitch. Despite its light weight and compact dimensions, the perceived recoil of the 7.62x39mm carbine proved to be quite pleasant and manageable. Accuracy at 100 yards was also quite good; particularly considering the fact the rifle was tested with only the iron sights.
• All VZ58 - 2008 rifles possess a milled receiver; the vast majority of AK-47s are stamped. 
• Even with the milled receiver it is almost one pound lighter than a stamped AK-47.
• The bolt of the VZ 2008 stays open after the last round in the magazine has been fired.
• The VZ 2008 can be reloaded with stripper clips while the magazine is inserted in the rifle.
• The safety is more ergonomic making a faster first shot possible with the VZ2008.
• The ejection port is HUGE. There is no chance of an empty case getting stuck in the action of the VZ2008.
• The VZ2008 gas piston can be removed or exchanged without tools.
• The alloy magazine of the VZ2008 is half the weight of the steel AK-47 magazine.
• The VZ2008 is striker fired unlike the hammer fired AK-47. This reduces the number of parts and possible points of failure.

• We've fired 700+ rounds through our store sample, no cleaning, no problems at all 
• Battle rifle accuracy that I am sure I could improve 
• At $535.00 this rifle is an absolute steal 
• Came with sling, 3 30 rd mags, and a cleaning kit 
• Minimal buildup after shooting 
• Easy to take down 
• Surplus parts available for low prices
